#BillLucy was a native Memphian and one of the last great Memphis civil rights warriors. He befriended me many years ago and gave me wise counsel. I greatly value being a recipient of the Bill Lucy Black Labor Award.

He was an architect of the 1968 Memphis @AFSCME  sanitation strike, which coined the iconic “I AM A MAN” posters, and advocated for better working conditions for Black Americans. He will forever be remembered as one of America’s greatest civil rights trailblazers.
